fidelity /fɪˈdɛlɪtɪ/

1. N-UNCOUNT Fidelity is loyalty to a person, organization, or set of beliefs. 忠诚 [正式] 

例： People have failed to act in fidelity to their vows. 人们没能忠诚地履行自己的誓言。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Fidelity is being loyal to your husband, wife, or partner by not having a sexual relationship with anyone else. 忠贞 

例： Women expect fidelity from their men. 女人期望来自她们男人的忠贞。

